  "prompt": "What is the average CPF cash balance for a member at the age of 55 in Singapore?",
  "response": "As of the latest available data up to 2023, the average Central Provident Fund (CPF) cash balance for Singaporean members at the age of 55 is approximately **SGD 100,000 to SGD 120,000**. \n\nHowever, it's important to note that this figure can vary significantly based on several factors, including:\n\n- **Employment History**: Length of time employed and consistent CPF contributions.\n- **Income Levels**: Higher earners generally contribute more to their CPF accounts.\n- **Investment Choices**: Utilization of CPF Investment Scheme (CPFIS) can impact the growth of CPF savings.\n- **Retirement Planning**: Individual strategies for retirement planning, including additional voluntary contributions.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's recommended to consult the **CPF Annual Report** or the **CPF website** directly:\n\n- **CPF Annual Reports**: [CPF Annual Reports](https://www.cpf.gov.sg/about-cpf/reports-statistics/annual-reports)\n- **CPF Website**: [Central Provident Fund (CPF)](https://www.cpf.gov.sg)\n\nThese resources provide comprehensive insights and detailed statistics about CPF savings, contributions, and projections tailored to different age groups and retirement needs.",
